\psi(\lambda u + (1-\lambda) v) = \lambda \psi(u) + (1-\lambda) \psi(v)
\lambda
\psi
\lambda(u) = \psi(u)-\psi(0)
\mathbb{R}^n
\lambda(u) = c_1 u_1+\cdots + c_n u_n = \langle c, u \rangle 
c \in \mathbb{R}^n
\lambda
c \neq 0
\alpha
\langle c, \alpha c \rangle = -\psi(0)
\psi(u) = \langle c, u-x \rangle
x= \alpha c
